subject: Basketball
College Athletics
lead_paragraph: Danielle McCray scored 20 points and No. 19 Kansas (2-0) used a late 11-0 run to win Wednesday night at Iowa, 66-55. All the Kansas starters scored in double figures. Kachine Alexander had 23 points and 17 rebounds to lead Iowa (2-1). Trailing by 54-51 with seven minutes to go, Kansas went on its run.
